Jappo Ligguey (asf) is a mixed association made up of several micro-entrepreneurs. It was created in 2009 by a group of women in order to regroup all their friends in the Angle Serigne Fallou (asf) neighborhood with the same ideal "mutual aid for working". It is managed by Mrs. Marie Ndiaye Diouf and split into several sub-groups of five under the auspices of the credit agent of the Moda Kane savings bank, so that all the members can benefit more easily from the services of U-IMCEC (a Senegalese association of mutual savings and loans institutions). Hence, certain sub-groups have requested a loan of 500,000FCFA, which will be shared out equally among their members; 

Jappo Liggey asf no. 5 is managed by the president, Mrs. Saly S.. She is a married woman who has a business selling couscous, which she has been making herself since 2006. With her 100,000FCFA portion of the loan, she is planning to strengthen her business by getting supplies of basic products to make couscous. She wants to buy millet, corn, peanut etc. This loan will thus allow her to renew her stock and make a higher profit from her business.

The loans will also allow the other sub-group members to strengthen their activities. Among others, they are: the treasurer, Mrs. Fatma Koné who has been active in the sale of second-hand clothing for two years; Mrs. Khady M., a vendor of ready-to-wear clothing at the central market in Thiès for the past two years; Mrs. Magatte M., who has been selling breakfasts and dinners in the front of her house for just one year; and finally Mrs. Fatou M. who has been managing a general grocery store for the past five years.  <br /><p><strong>Translated from French by Alison Le Bras, Kiva Volunteer</strong></p>
